Detailed Description

CphsAuxProvider is the provider to retrieve different kind of data relating to the Cphs extension of the Gsm standard from the mobile station. An instance of this class is part of the Apoxi Data Control. A pointer to this provider can be retrieved from the main provider via the id:

c_cphs_aux_provider_id

Following column ids are defined: c_cphs_phase_id :NumberType: CPHS Phase as defined in CPHS4_2.WW6 B3.1.1 c_infnrs_activated_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN if service is activated c_infnrs_allocated_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN if service is allocated c_csp_activated_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN if service is activated c_csp_allocated_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN if service is allocated c_sst_activated_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN if service is activated c_sst_allocated_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN if service is allocated c_mboxnrs_activated_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN if service is activated c_mboxnrs_allocated_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN if service is allocated c_opname_activated_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN if service is activated c_opname_allocated_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN if service is allocated c_operator_name_id :WStringType: operator name as defined in CPHS4_2.WW6 B.4.1.2 c_operator_shortname_id :WStringType: operator name with max. 10 Chars as defined in CPHS4_2.WW6 B.4.1.2 c_msg_wait_ind_line1_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN if msg is waiting c_msg_wait_ind_line2_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN if msg is waiting c_msg_wait_ind_fax_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN if msg is waiting c_msg_wait_ind_data_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN if msg is waiting c_call_fwd_line1_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN if call forwarding unconditional is active c_call_fwd_line2_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN if call forwarding unconditional is active c_call_fwd_fax_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN if call forwarding unconditional is active c_call_fwd_data_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN if call forwarding unconditional is active c_line_in_use_id :NumberType: 0 if Line1 is used, 1 if Line2 is used (meaning of byte on SIM is reverse) c_line_is_locked_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN, if TRUE the line is locked c_cphs_is_present_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN, if TRUE CPHS is supported c_orange_welcome_msg_id :WStringType: returns the Orange welcome message

This provider only consists of one fixed row.

NOTE: Please do not instantiate this class.
